Fix #1401, trace servlet parameter handling (#1409)

* corrected servlet parameter handling so that it does not break things

This resolves #1401.

I removed the previous implementation of  string sanitization, replacing it with more specific checks at the places where the parameters are used.

BasicTest was deleted because it was exclusively testing the broken
sanitization mechanism.

Added null check to avoid NPE

ACCUMULO-4760 Fix NPE in Monitor replication rest

Update to HTrace 3.2

API fixes specifically for HTrace version 3.2:

* Use String-based annotations, instead of deprecated byte arrays API
* Update thrift and other utils to support multiple span parents and
more explicit tracking of root spans (those without parents)
* Remove broken API call to set the Tracer processId field

General fixes found broken, or generally lacking with 3.2, but were in
need of fix anyway:

* Properly close spans, via containing TraceScope instead of trying to
manually stop and set it to null by messing with HTrace internal
tracking (avoid doing Tracer.getInstance().continueSpan(null), since the
resulting Closeable can't be closed, because it throws an NPE)
* Ensure TraceScopes are closed via try-with-resources wherever we were
manually trying to stop the span
* Explicitly support client-side tracing in various command-line tools
by parsing arguments with an option to return a TraceScope object, which
is then put in a try-with-resources block

Trivial unrelated changes:
